## Current Content

There currently are about **{{planes}}** unique aircraft in **{{categories}}** categories found in this repository.
These aircraft are divided into two main databases:

-   [plane-alert-db.csv](data/plane-alert-db.csv) - A list of interesting aircraft with tags, categories and links. ({{plane_alert_db}})
-   [plane-alert-pia.csv](data/plane-alert-pia.csv) - A list that contains Privacy ICAO Address (PIA) planes. ({{plane_alert_pia}})

Based on these main databases, several derivative databases are created automatically by a [GitHub Action](.github/workflows/create_db_derivatives.yaml):

-   [plane-alert-civ.csv](data/plane-alert-civ.csv) - Civilian Registered Aircraft, includes Historic and Distinctive. ({{civ_count}})
-   [plane-alert-mil.csv](data/plane-alert-mil.csv) - Military Only. ({{mil_count}})
-   [plane-alert-pol.csv](data/plane-alert-pol.csv) - Police Forces. ({{pol_count}})
-   [plane-alert-gov.csv](data/plane-alert-gov.csv) - Governments, Gov Agencies and Dictators. ({{gov_count}})

## Description of Categories

Categories follow an aviation-taxonomy scheme so that any aircraft in the database can be classified by what it *is*, rather than by personality or group membership.

|**Category**|**Description**|
|--------|-----------|
|AEW&C|Airborne Early Warning and Control aircraft (E-3 Sentry, E-2 Hawkeye, A-50, etc.)|
|Attack / Strike|Ground-attack and strike aircraft (A-10, B-1B, B-52, AV-8B Harrier, A-4 Skyhawk, etc.)|
|Business Jet|Corporate and executive jets (Gulfstream, Learjet, Falcon, Challenger, Global, etc.)|
|Cargo Freighter|Dedicated cargo / freighter aircraft|
|Electronic Warfare|Dedicated EW and jamming aircraft (EA-18G, Tornado ECR, EC-130H Compass Call, etc.)|
|Fighter / Interceptor|Air-superiority and multi-role fighters (F-16, F-15, Eurofighter Typhoon, Gripen, Mirage, etc.)|
|Helicopter - Attack|Attack and armed helicopters (AH-64 Apache, etc.)|
|Helicopter - Maritime|Maritime patrol and naval helicopters (Lynx, Merlin, Ka-27, AS565 Panther, etc.)|
|Helicopter - Transport|Medium- and heavy-lift transport helicopters (UH-60, CH-47 Chinook, NH90, Mi-17, AS332, etc.)|
|Helicopter - Utility|Light and utility helicopters (EC135, EC145, Bell 206/407, Bo 105, AW109, etc.)|
|ISR / Surveillance|Intelligence, Surveillance and Reconnaissance aircraft (U-2, RC-135, Il-20, E-8 J-STARS, etc.)|
|Maritime Patrol|Maritime patrol and anti-submarine aircraft (P-8 Poseidon, P-3 Orion, Atlantique, etc.)|
|Passenger - Narrowbody|Single-aisle airliner variants (A320 family, 737 family, Tu-154, Tu-134, etc.)|
|Passenger - Widebody|Twin-aisle airliner variants (A330, A340, 747, 767, 777, 787, Il-96, etc.)|
|Regional Passenger|Regional airliners and turboprops (ERJ, CRJ, DHC-8, SAAB 340, Beech 1900, etc.)|
|Special Mission|Specialized aircraft not covered by other categories (CL-415 water bombers, C-2 Greyhound, V-22 Osprey, historic warbirds, etc.)|
|Strategic Airlift|Large strategic transport aircraft (C-17, C-5, An-124, Il-76, Y-20, etc.)|
|Tactical Airlift|Medium tactical transport aircraft (C-130, A400M, C-27J, C-295, An-26, Let L-410, etc.)|
|Tanker|Aerial refuelling tankers (KC-135, KC-10, KC-46, A310 MRTT, etc.)|
|Trainer|Military and civilian training aircraft (T-38, PC-21, PC-9, T-6 Texan, Alpha Jet, Chipmunk, etc.)|
|UAV - Combat|Armed unmanned aerial vehicles|
|UAV - Recon|Reconnaissance and surveillance UAVs (MQ-4C Triton, RQ-7 Shadow, etc.)|
|UAV - Utility|Utility and logistics UAVs|
|Utility|Aircraft with a general utility role that do not fit a more specific category (King Air, PC-12, Caravan, light aircraft, etc.)|

Each aircraft also carries up to three structured tags:

- **Tag 1** — primary mission role (e.g. *Tactical Transport*, *ISR*, *Air Superiority*, *Training*)
- **Tag 2** — capability or configuration (e.g. *Long Range*, *STOL*, *Heavy Lift*, *Carrier Capable*)
- **Tag 3** — propulsion or airframe (e.g. *Twin Turboprop*, *Rotorcraft*, *Quad Engine*, *Rear Ramp*)

## CSV Format

The list takes the form:

| $ICAO  | $Registration | $Operator           | $Type               | $ICAO Type | #CMPG | $Tag 1   | $#Tag 2   | $#Tag 3 | Category |
| ------ | ------------- | ------------------- | ------------------- | ---------- | ----- | -------- | --------- | ------- | -------- |
| 502C5C | YL-KSH        | Baltic Bees display team | Aero L-39C Albatros | L39       | Civ   | Training | Multi-Role | Jet    | Trainer  |

Column prefix conventions:

-   `$` - Tweet this column as #hashtag.
-   `#` - Hidden from display (the ICAO field is always shown regardless).
-   `$#` - Hidden from display and tweeted as a #hashtag.

## Contributing

Feel free to [open an issue](https://github.com/FugginOld/plane-alert-db-normalized/issues) if you have ideas on improving this repository or want to report a bug! All contributions are welcome 🚀. Please consult the [contribution guidelines](CONTRIBUTING.md) for more information. You can also check out the [TODOS](TODOS.md) page if you want to contribute to this repository but need some ideas.

> **Warning**
> As also [explained above](#current-content), this repository has two main databases to which people can contribute: `plane-alert-db.csv` and `plane-alert-pia.csv`. The derivative databases (`civ`, `mil`, `pol`, `gov`) are created automatically by a [GitHub Action](.github/workflows/create_db_derivatives.yaml) and must not be edited directly — any manual changes will be overwritten. Additionally, it is **not recommended** to edit the CSV files in Microsoft Excel, as Excel will attempt to "fix" some ICAO hexes and other fields. Use a code editor such as VS Code instead—press the period key `.` on any file in GitHub to open the web editor.

If you're creating a pull request with additions, please add them to the end of the file. We may sort the list periodically to group like planes together.

